%20a%20dozen%20helicopters%2C%20an%20air-defense%20launcher%2C%20vehicles%2C%20and%20ammunition.%20This%20particular%20ATACMS%20variant%20is%20powerful%2C%20has%20a%20range%20of%20around%20100%20miles%2C%20and%20is%20packed%20with%20950%20anti-personnel%20and%20anti-materiel%2C%20or%20APAM%2C%20M74%20bomblets%20%E2%80%94%20small%20submunitions%20that%20scatter%20and%20disperse%20mid-flight%20over%20a%20large%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMykola%20Bielieskov%2C%20a%20research%20fellow%20at%20Ukraine's%20National%20Institute%20for%20Strategic%20Studies%2C%20said%20the%20M39%20variant%20is%20effective%20against%20%26quot%3Bunprotected%20targets%26quot%3B%20like%20helicopters%2C%20air-defense%20systems%2C%20and%20ammunition%20depots.%20He%20said%20Russian%20military%20leadership%20will%20likely%20now%20look%20to%20pull%20back%20vulnerable%20and%20prized%20targets%20to%20the%20rear.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20%26quot%3Bare%20practical%20limitations%20on%20how%20much%20Russian%20military%20equipment%20can%20be%20pulled%20back%20without%20leaving%20front%20line%20troops%20vulnerable%2C%26quot%3B%20Bielieskov%20wrote%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlanticcouncil.org%2Fblogs%2Fukrainealert%2Fatacms-missiles-create-new-dilemmas-for-russian-army-in-ukraine%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommentary%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20on%20Tuesday%20by%20the%20Atlantic%20Council%2C%20a%20Washington-based%20think%20tank.%C2%A0One%20example%20of%20this%2C%20he%20pointed%20to%2C%20is%20Russia's%20reliance%20on%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-ka52m-helicopters-long-range-anti-tank-missile-ukraine-uk-2023-7%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%3Ehelicopters%20to%20defend%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20Ukrainian%20counteroffensive%20that%20began%20in%20early%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20data-lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20class%